<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>1105</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-003U</addr>  <route>axt-003U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>13</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jean-goubault-larrecq.xml" type="local">Jean Goubault-Larrecq</link></author> </authors> <title>Alexandroff topology</title> <meta name="source"><b>Prop. 4.2.11</b> of <link href="jgl-non-hausdorff.xml" type="local" title="Non-Hausdorff topology and domain theory">Goubault-Larrecq</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>A</tex> be a preordered set. A subset <tex>U  \subseteq  A</tex> is taken as an open in
